report.measDesc: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either tools in ArcGIS or ESRI SDC Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2). The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify and validate the geometry.
After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

Horizontal positional accuracy is dependent on geographic area. In most areas, accuracy is between 5 and 25 meters (16 and 82 feet). In some areas, accuracy is off by up to several tens of meters (100 feet or more). In the poorest areas, accuracy is off by up to 100 meters (328 feet).

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the state data set from Tele Atlas MultiNet Administrative Areas v. 2010.03. Clipped the coastline with the Tele Atlas MultiNet North America water data set. Removed the U.S. Virgin Islands. Attached and formatted the fields from 2009 Data Update U.S. States. Replaced field POP2009 with POP2010 and field POP09_SQMI with POP10_SQMI. Renamed the four agriculture fields to NO_FARMS07, AVG_SIZE07, CROP_ACR07, and AVG_SALE07 and got new values from the 2007 Census of Agriculture. Put "-99" values into all number type fields (except SQMI) for records where there were no matches. Calculated new values for fields POP00_SQMI, POP10_SQMI, and SQMI from the MultiNet field FEATAREA. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.
